Issue with classification


12 Jun 2020 22:20






I do enjoy the trope of a single human containing an anomaly, but making them into a Thaumiel for it is kinda unnecessary to me. Thaumiel-class anomalies are usually much larger scale ones, such as preventing worldwide disasters or providing immense aid to the Foundation. A single human - especially a non-anomalous one - containing a single anomaly doesn't really fit into that criteria for me. Could be just a personal opinion, but still.







